<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at the trail • on the trail</xh5><p> <i>at the trail</i>—(Military) carrying a rifle in the right hand, the arm at full length, and the gun horizontal: The volunteers are in step, rifles are carried uniformly horizontal <u>at the “trail</u>.” </p><p><i>on the trail—</i>1. following a path in a wild or uninhabited region: In discrete valleys were a few cabins, and they stayed in them or <i>siwashed </i>(camped <u>on the trail</u>). 2. following traces or tracks in hunting: Jacob’s dog leads them into the woods <u>on the trail</u> of a fox, and there they come upon the wreckage of a small plane. 3. following smb.; in pursuit of a person: The police are <u>on the trail</u> of a group of Satanists, believed to have caused a young man’s death.</p> </entry>
